From: cyy <cyyever@gmail.com>
Subject: [PATCH] macOS: msync fast-sync (CrossOver port + macOS integration)

Consolidated msync subsystem patch. Merges what were separate patches
(0008 core + 0016 msg_queue wake) plus the socket-async / system-APC
lost-wake fix that lets Steam log in with WINEMSYNC=1:

  - msync fast-sync core (CrossOver port; ~msync.c client+server, de-linux)
  - msync mixed-wait hybrid (msync_wait_mixed_any: bounded server poll on the
    server subset of a mixed msync+server wait set), plus an event-driven
    WINEMSYNC_UNIFIED variant (server-side "bridge": msync_register_bridge /
    msync_unregister_bridge subscribe a client bridge auto-event to a set of
    server objects so the client blocks once instead of polling)
  - per-object msync idx for waits; the earlier "uniform inproc_sync shadow"
    approach was mismatched to macOS (msync objects are pure shm+__ulock with no
    fd, so the server can't wait on them) and is dropped:
      * server/object.c default_get_sync() returns the object itself, not an
        msync shadow (a shadow made server-side waits hit no_add_queue ->
        STATUS_OBJECT_TYPE_MISMATCH, breaking socket() / Steam PlatformSocketsInit)
      * server/msync.c get_msync_idx handler uses the object's own get_msync_idx
        ops slot (gated on the sync being non-server-waitable), not the
        ntsync-only get_obj_inproc_sync() which is stubbed on macOS
  - msg_queue wake consistency (was 0016): msync_wake_up()/msync_clear() fall
    back to the queue's own get_msync_idx when get_obj_inproc_sync() returns -1
    for the queue's server-backed event_sync on macOS, so a GUI message wait
    isn't left with a lost wakeup ("not responding" webhelper)
  - socket-async / system-APC lost-wake fix: a system APC (APC_ASYNC_IO from a
    socket/file async completion) is delivered by SIGUSR1, which interrupts a
    msync fast-wait (-EINTR / KERN_ABORTED); the fast path can't see it, so
    without draining it the APC never runs and the awaited object never signals
    (Steam socket I/O hung -> "Unexpected Transport Error"). msync_run_system_apcs()
    does a 0-timeout interruptible server_wait to run any pending system APC.
    Verified: Steam completes full CM logon under WINEMSYNC=1.
  - server-side event-on-msync guard: with events on msync, get_event_obj()
    hands req_event_op/query_event a msync object cast as `struct event`, whose
    ->sync field is garbage. Both handlers now branch on obj.ops == &msync_ops
    (like set_event/reset_event already did) and read state via
    msync_get_event_state()/msync_is_manual_event() instead of dereferencing
    ->sync -- fixes an EXC_BAD_ACCESS wineserver crash under full msync.
    (Auto-reset events on msync still have a consume-race spin -- run them on
    server-sync with WINEMSYNC_NO_AUTOEVENT=1; everything else stays on msync.)

do_msync() respects WINEMSYNC (default on). Builds x86_64 under Rosetta.

This patch is self-contained: it also ships the generated protocol files
(include/wine/server_protocol.h, server/request_handlers.h,
server/request_trace.h) regenerated from server/protocol.def, since only this
patch modifies protocol.def -- so a fresh apply needs no make_requests step.

